TY  - JOUR
AU  - Viale, Ariel M.
AU  - Garcia-Feijoo, Luis
AU  - Giannetti, Antoine
T1  - Safety First, Learning Under Ambiguity, and the Cross-Section of Stock Returns
PY  - 2014
Y1  - 2014/06/01
DO  - 10.1093/rapstu/rat017
JO  - The Review of Asset Pricing Studies
JA  - Rev Asset Pric Stud
VL  - 4
IS  - 1
SP  - 118
EP  - 159
SN  - 2045-9920
AB  - We examine the empirical implications of learning under ambiguity for the cross-section of stock returns. We introduce a theoretically-motivated ambiguity measure and find that ambiguity is priced in the cross-section of average stock returns. Ambiguity is not subsumed by state variables known to predict stock returns, nor by value, size, and momentum factors. In R-squared comparative tests, a model that takes ambiguity into account performs better than empirical implementations of the Bayesian learning model, the intertemporal CAPM, and the four-factor model of Fama and French (1993) and Carhart (1997). (JEL G12)
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rapstu/rat017
ER  - 



